  "texts": [
    "Current works in progress follow the same path to overcome these obstacles and optimize the performances of the AI-based anomaly detection technique to guarantee the safety of telecommunication networks (Umoga et al. 2024).",
    "AI anomaly detection is the identification of recurrent patterns that do not fall within the standard range through the use of artificial intelligence and machine learning.",
    "Compared to the conventional methods, AI anomaly detection does not solely operate based on some fixed levels or basic mathematical approaches.",
    "It utilizes models that make use of learning from the data presented to them and can adapt to changes in patterns (Himeur et al. 2021).",
    "The most commonly employed procedure encompasses data intake, extractive transformation, model development, and further observation."
  ],
